{meta: title Someone Took My Place With You}
{meta: artist Earl Scruggs and Lester Flatt}
{meta: writer Lester Flatt, Earl Scruggs, Gurney Thomas}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]Now someone took my place with [D7]you
[G]Now you tell me we are through
[D7]Someone broke my heart in two
[G]When they took my place with you
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[C]Now someone left me here to [G]cry
[D7]And with each day that passes by
[G]Now I'm found here alone and [D7]blue
[G]Cause someone took my place with you
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[D7]In days to come I know you'll find
[G]When you've left me here behind
[D7]Someday I'm sure that you will find
[G]You wrecked your life as well as mine
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
